## Tagging Convention

### Standard Feature File Tag Structure
```gherkin
@BizomWebAPI @[CategoryTag] @[ModuleName] @[AdditionalTags]
Feature: [Feature Description]
```

### Example
```gherkin
@BizomWebAPI @MasterDataManagement @ReasonsManagement @GetReasonTypeData
Feature: Get Reason Type Data API Testing
```

## Execution

### Run tests by category:
- `@CoreBusinessOperations` - Execute all core business operation tests
- `@MasterDataManagement` - Execute all master data management tests
- `@ConfigurationSettings` - Execute all configuration and settings tests
- `@ReportsAnalytics` - Execute all reports and analytics tests
- `@SupportingFunctions` - Execute all supporting function tests

### Combined execution:
- `@CoreBusinessOperations,@MasterDataManagement` - Execute both categories
- `@BizomWebAPI` - Execute all tests (includes all categories)

## Adding New Feature Files

When creating a new feature file:
1. Identify the management directory it belongs to
2. Refer to this document to determine the appropriate category tag
3. Add the category tag as the second tag (after @BizomWebAPI)
4. Follow the standard tagging convention

## Maintenance

This document should be updated when:
- New management directories are added
- Existing directories are reorganized
- Tag categories need to be adjusted
